{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"halfbare-tsaristic-barnacle","description":"## Why\n\nThe plan-review `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecar is the only durable record of a review's four passes, but\nits `_slim` step drops the pass-1 `evidence` and `scenarios` fields, and it does not persist the\nnumeric `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` each finding was judged against (these are resolved\nfrom the criteria registry at decision time and then discarded). Without them an auditor cannot see\na finding's grounding quotes or the exact decision boundary that was applied.\n\n## What\n\nExtend the plan-review sidecar to a new schema version `plan_review_result_v2` that additionally\npersists, per finding: the pass-1 `evidence[]` and `scenarios[]`, and the resolved `block_threshold`\n(float) and `blocking_enabled` (bool) that pass-3 used. All existing fields and the all-buckets\npooling (blocking + advisory + overflow + indeterminate + dropped) are unchanged.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py` â€” bump `SCHEMA` to `plan_review_result_v2`; stop stripping\n  `evidence`/`scenarios` in `_slim`; thread the resolved `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled` from\n  the pass-3 decision into each persisted finding; `latest_review_result` accepts both `v1` and `v2`.\n- `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/decide.py` â€” expose the resolved `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled`\n  on each finding's decision output (the `ThresholdResolver` result is currently used then dropped).\n\n## Approach rationale\n\nBump the schema and widen the payload rather than write a parallel record, so the single existing\nemit/prune/read path carries the richer data unchanged in shape. The resolved threshold is captured\nat the exact point pass-3 applies it, which is the only place it is knowable without re-reading the\nregistry (avoiding historical drift).\n\n## Compatibility & rollback\n\n`v1` sidecars remain valid and are read with the new fields absent (readers treat missing\nthreshold/evidence as \"not recorded\"). No backfill. Reverting restores the `v1` payload; already-\nwritten `v2` events remain readable by the tolerant reader. Adding fields to the payload does not\nchange the reducer-ignored status or the event type, so older clients keep skipping the event.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Running `review-plan` emits a `REVIEW_RESULT` event whose `schema` is `plan_review_result_v2`\n      and whose every persisted finding carries `evidence`, `scenarios`, `block_threshold`, and\n      `blocking_enabled`. Oracle: an in-process integration test drives a review with a stub LLM\n      runner and asserts on the emitted event JSON via the real sidecar emit path (test-design Â§3\n      producer/consumer shape).\n- [ ] `pass3_decide`/`pass3_over_findings` expose the resolved `block_threshold`/`blocking_enabled`\n      on each finding. Oracle: a unit test against the real decide functions asserting the fields\n      are present with the resolved values.\n- [ ] `latest_review_result` reads both a `v1` and a `v2` sidecar file without error, reporting the\n      new fields absent for `v1`. Oracle: a unit test feeding one hand-written `v1` and one `v2`\n      event.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass.","id":"4e19-5846-0e3f-4882","parent_id":"ba33-2310-f6c6-4bd6","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"plan-review sidecar -> lossless v2 (evidence, scenarios, thresholds)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784067232188658001,"uuid":"9a6658f2-5614-4a4f-9831-57834946304d"}